    "Partial revert of b364 V-first routing + tighter armor scroll catchup (build 365). Build-364 7000T validation sweep: vendor visits only crept +0.08/run (real ceiling is ~0.45 V/floor = V spawn rate, not policy priority) AND F5 gear quality REGRESSED atk+def 16.8 -> 12.9 because V-first routing pulled agents to vendors gold-poor (575-688g human/elf) before chest+kill loot accumulated. Reverted V back to its b363 tier-1 position in default / ready_to_clear / unvisited_beneficials branches -- agents now collect chest gold first, then visit V with money to spend. Kept V-first in high_coverage_descend only: this is the LAST chance to shop before leaving the floor, gold isn't going to grow further. Plus armor-scroll tuning: ARMOR_CATCHUP_GAP dropped 2 -> 1 (true round-robin). B364 data: dwarf weapon_UL=1.25 vs armor_UL=0.42 (3:1), too weapon-biased given runs only read ~2 scrolls total before death. Round-robin should bring armor_UL up so the F5-F7 wall's defensive scaling actually shows.",
    "V (vendor) promoted to top priority on every floor (build 364). User framing: 'it's pretty much the top priority of any level to find the vendor and buy all the items'. Build-363 sweep showed 2.2-3.3 vendor visits per run -- agents were still skipping vendors when high_coverage_descend / unvisited_beneficials / ready_to_clear / default branches gave V tier 2-3 priority behind D or BENEFICIAL_SAFE. Now V is the first tier in every non-emergency branch: high_coverage_descend, ready_to_clear, unvisited_beneficials, and default. V only loses priority to (1) trapped_no_d / retreat / too_long_on_floor escapes, (2) is_weak (still V first), (3) wants_vendor (still V first). Once V is visited it leaves feature_paths so the priority becomes moot for the rest of the floor. Vendor_shop policy already buys upgrade scrolls first (cap 5) + the full repair / stockpile / equipment-upgrade / scroll-buy pipeline, so the win is purely in routing -- the agent now stops in at the shop on its way to the stairs instead of past them.",
    "Plug FLOOR_STUCK_TURNS + wants_vendor leaks in the grind gate (build 363). Build-362 validation sweep found two leaks past the new gates: (1) FLOOR_STUCK_TURNS=300 in both the game_loop and stairs_down policies fired regardless of level/gear -- 6 of 11 F6+ stair descents hit this override on weakly-geared agents (s=11 human F5-&gt;F6 at T888, kof=6/11, atk+def=22). (2) wants_gear_upgrade only fired on starter Dagger/Leather, so F3+ agents on Short Sword (atk+4) didn't actively pull to V even though weakly_geared treated them as not-ready-to-descend. Fixes: stuck threshold now tiered -- ready agents release at 300T, under-levelled OR weakly-geared agents get 800T (mirrored in both game_loop FLOOR_STUCK_TURNS and stairs_down `stuck`). wants_gear_upgrade extends to weakly_geared_v + 60g (Mace tier). Vendor visits 2.2-2.8/run should rise; F5 stair-bail at sub-13 atk+def should close. Multi-floor warp leak (resist-fail on under-levelled agents) acknowledged but not addressed -- the policy is already correctly returning 'y'; the resist roll itself is INT-gated. Separate fix.",
    "Tighter grind / gear gates to slow descent on the F5-F7 wall (build 362). Build-360 10000T sweep: every race plateaued at F5-F7 with 74% of deaths being -HP combat losses, food still in belly. Agents were meeting the old descend gate (level == floor on-pace, 9 kills at F5, no gear-quality check) and walking onto F6 monsters tuned for combined atk+def 11-12 while still wearing Short Sword (4) + Ring Mail (4). Three tighter gates land together: (1) under_leveled now `level <= z+2` (was `<= z+1`) -- F5 needs Lv7 minimum, not Lv6. (2) min_kills_for_floor curve bumped to min(15, max(3, z*2+3)): F1=3, F3=7, F5=11, F7=15. (3) New `weakly_geared` gate from F3+: equipped weapon.attack_bonus + armor.defense_bonus must clear 2*z+3 (F3>=9, F5>=13, F7>=17), keeping the agent at vendors / chests / blacksmiths / shrines until the loadout actually scales. All three gates fold into grind_complete, the avoid-D set, and the stairs_down step-off so the agent can't slip past via any path. Smoke-tested: human/s42 stayed on F1 to T300 banking XP + gold (was descending by T80 on build 361), dwarf/s5 healthy at F5 HP 83/86 at T800.",
    "Growth Mushroom path also strips bug gear (build 361). Build-360 closed the SHRINK side of the gear-symmetry bug, but the 10000T sweep on build 360 found the inverse: items.py:1221 Growth Mushroom flips gs.player_is_shrunk=False directly without going through _restore_size_on_bug_exit, so eating the Mushroom leaves bug Weapon/Armor equipped on a now-normal-sized character. Concrete repro from human/s7: T1927 eats Mushroom, shrunk-&gt;False, Chitin Shell (bug, def_bonus=6) stays equipped for 225T alongside Obsidian Edge then Soul Reaver. Fix: Growth Mushroom now mirrors _restore_size_on_bug_exit's bug-gear unequip block (drop equipped Stinger Blade / Chitin Shell etc., items stay in inventory for re-entry). Smoke-tested seed=7 human: shrink -&gt; equip Stinger+Chitin -&gt; eat Mushroom -&gt; weapon=None, armor=None, both bug items still in inv, re-equip blocked while big-sized.",
    "Shrink auto-unequips normal-size gear (build 360). User-reported bug: Bombur Axebreaker (s=10 dwarf) wound up with Adamantine Armor + Scorpion Tail Whip co-equipped -- normal-size armor and bug-size weapon at the same time. Root cause: the equip gate at game_systems.py:2263 only blocks NEW equips of the wrong size, not gear that was already equipped before the size change. _restore_size_on_bug_exit already drops bug gear when growing back, but the SHRINK direction had no symmetric unequip -- so a player descending into a bug floor in full Adamantine kit kept the armor through the shrink, then swapped the weapon slot to a bug weapon and ended up in a mixed state. Fix: _trigger_shrinking_spell now unequips any non-bug Weapon/Armor at the moment of shrinking, with flavor logs ('suddenly enormous in your tiny hands', 'slides off your shrunken frame'). Items stay in inventory so they auto-re-equip on grow-back.",
